snippet.textDisplay:
LIGHT Genesis 1:3, 4
As I have probably said before the concept that GOD created light as a separate entity on day one never really hit me until a few years ago as me and my daughter worked on her grade school creation project. Light wasn’t coming from the sun (it wasn’t made yet) and not even from GOD. Scientists have been fascinated with light ever since Einstein made it a cornerstone of his theories. Light illuminates, has been ‘clocked’ at 299,792,488 meters per second, is used to measure distance in space, and long after a star dies its light is still seen. If JESUS made such a wonder filled thing then He must be a wonderful GOD. Praise Him.
